encrypt() always prefixes ciphertext with keyIndex "0" even when ENCRYPTION_KEY contains multiple keys. That makes the documented `keyIndex:<iv>:<authTag>:<ciphertext>` format misleading and prevents decrypt() from using the index as an accurate hint after key rotation (it will always try key 0 first). Consider encoding a stable key identifier/fingerprint (or the actual key slot used) instead of hardcoding 0, or update the format/docs accordingly.

--- inline by @Copilot at 2026-03-20T23:02:54Z on core/security/blindIndex.ts:22 ---
blindIndex() derives its HMAC key from only the *primary* ENCRYPTION_KEY and doesn’t validate the key format/length. If/when ENCRYPTION_KEY is rotated (new key prepended), blindIndex outputs will change and any stored hashes (e.g., emailHash/tokenHash) will no longer match lookups unless you migrate/backfill or support multi-key verification. Recommend (1) validating the key like encryption.ts does, and (2) adding a rotation strategy for blind indexes (e.g., store key id alongside the hash or provide a helper to compute candidate hashes for all configured keys during lookup).

